module ldpc348_91_mod

! LDPC(348,91) rate-compatible mother code for FT1 IR-HARQ.
!
! Construction: Parity extension of LDPC(174,91).
!   - First 174 columns: identical to LDPC(174,91)
!   - Columns 175-261: RV1 extension parity (87 new bits)
!   - Columns 262-348: RV2 extension parity (87 new bits)
!
! H matrix structure (257 rows x 348 columns):
!   Rows   1- 83: original LDPC(174,91) H, zero-padded to 348 cols
!   Rows  84-170: extension rows connecting cols 175-261 to systematic bits
!   Rows 171-257: extension rows connecting cols 262-348 to systematic bits
!
! Nested rate-compatible codes:
!   LDPC(174,91): rate 0.523 (RV0 only)
!   LDPC(261,91): rate 0.349 (RV0 + RV1)
!   LDPC(348,91): rate 0.261 (RV0 + RV1 + RV2)
!
! Extension rows use PEG-optimized connections. Each new parity bit is
! connected to 5 columns from the base code (both systematic and parity
! bits), chosen by Progressive Edge Growth to maximize local girth (>=6)
! and balance column weights.
!
! Reference: specs/3d_protocol.md Section 8.2, ir_harq_protocol_design.md
! Generated by: research/phase2/gen_ldpc348_91.py

